Eigen 5.0.0 renamed the Eigen/Core include guard from EIGEN_CORE_H to
EIGEN_CORE_MODULE_H, so the Eigen-aware safemath helpers (safe_normalized)
silently vanish when building against Eigen >= 5: every consumer fails with
"safe_normalized is not a member of eonc::safemath". Accept either guard.
Author: Rohit Goswami <rgoswami@ieee.org>
--- a/client/SafeMath.h	2026-07-10 06:23:36.684883279 -0500
+++ b/client/SafeMath.h	2026-07-10 06:23:36.685561963 -0500
@@ -51,7 +51,7 @@
 
 // Eigen-dependent utilities, available only when Eigen is already included.
 // Include order: Eigen headers first, then SafeMath.h.
-#ifdef EIGEN_CORE_H
+#if defined(EIGEN_CORE_H) || defined(EIGEN_CORE_MODULE_H)
 namespace eonc::safemath {
 
 template <typename Derived>
